Command Center Glossary
FEATURE	WHAT TO LOOK OUT FOR
Filters	
Make sure to include all the data you want. To change a report filter, hover over it and click Edit or Remove.
Groupings	
When you group by a field, you remove it from the details of the report. If you export the report, you see the field, though it doesn’t appear in the detail area.
Fields	
After checking your groupings, check your fields. Ensure that the data is available in the format you want.
Report Type	
The report type selected isn't appropriate or the records anticipated don't share the relationship between objects required for the report type.
Hierarchy	
Hierarchy options let you drill down to different datasets based on the role or user hierarchy.
External Objects	
If your report includes an external object, the results probably don’t reflect the full dataset.
